= FactHarbor cooperation with UCH/ETH =

{{info}}
**Meeting:** UZH — 18 March 2026
**Participants:** Elliott Ash (ETHZ), Tobias Schimanski (UZH), Robert Schaub (FactHarbor)
{{/info}}

== Meeting Goal ==

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**During this hour, we want to:**
* show clearly what FactHarbor already does well and where the most research-relevant gaps still are
* test collaboration fit with the UZH / ETH-adjacent research context around **source attribution**, **relevance scoring**, **evaluation**, **reproducibility**, **speed**, and **cost**
* discuss whether an **Innosuisse-oriented applied innovation path** could realistically anchor the collaboration

**By the end of the meeting, we want to reach:**
* a shared view on whether there is a strong collaboration fit
* a short list of the most promising joint topics
* clarity on sensible next steps, such as a follow-up discussion, thesis / evaluation work, and possible project framing
)))

= FactHarbor =

Open-source applications and web services for AI-powered fact-checking — every verdict backed by evidence you can inspect.
(((
(% class="box infomessage" style="background-color: #fde0e4; color: #b71c1c;" %)
(((
**Mission:**
FactHarbor brings clarity and transparency to a world full of unclear, contested, and misleading information by shedding light on the context, assumptions, and evidence behind claims.
)))
)))

(% class="box warningmessage" %)
(((
**Non-profit and Transparent**
FactHarbor is a **Non-Profit Organisation** and a strictly **Open-Source** project.
We serve the public interest with full transparency — no hidden algorithms, and no profit motive.
)))

== Financing Options ==

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Possible project vehicle:** We are currently considering and investigating an Innosuisse-based collaboration route, framed as an applied innovation project with clear transfer into practice and a concrete implementation partner. Around that core, co-supervised Bachelor/Master theses, postdoc-scale evaluation work, and later SNSF / BRIDGE / Horizon follow-on projects could extend the research side.
)))

(% class="box infomessage" style="background-color:#eef3f8;border-color:#9db4cb;" %)
(((
**Released operation needs separate financing:** Research funding can support development, evaluation, and transfer work, but long-term public operation of a released service needs its own sustainability model. Plausible options include institutional partnerships, public-interest foundation grants, professional service / API contracts, community support, and infrastructure sponsors such as cloud or LLM-credit programmes.
)))
----

== FactHarbor Analysis Pipeline ==

A user submits any claim or article, in any language. The system extracts verifiable assertions, researches supporting and opposing evidence from real web sources, runs a structured AI debate, and produces a transparent verdict — every conclusion traceable to its sources.


{{mermaid}}
flowchart TD
    subgraph MAIN [" "]
        direction LR
        INPUT(["Your Claim<br/>or Article"])
        A["Extract<br/>verifiable claims"]:::ai

        B["Search supporting<br/>and opposing evidence"]:::web

        Q["Filter quality<br/>and score reliability"]:::ai
        C["Organize into<br/>evidence-defined boundaries"]:::ai

        subgraph DEBATE ["Structured AI Debate"]
            direction TB
            D["Advocate"]:::ai
            SC["Self-Consistency"]:::ai
            E["Challenger"]:::ai
            F["Reconciler"]:::ai
            V["Validator"]:::ai
            D --> SC & E
            SC & E --> F --> V
        end

        OUTPUT(["Verdict and<br/>Structured Report"])

        INPUT --> A --> B --> Q --> C --> DEBATE --> OUTPUT
    end

    subgraph LEGEND ["Legend"]
        direction LR
        L1["AI-powered"]:::ai ~~~ L2["Web and External Sources"]:::web
    end

    MAIN ~~~ LEGEND

    style INPUT fill:#2196F3,stroke:#1565C0,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    style OUTPUT fill:#4CAF50,stroke:#2E7D32,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    style DEBATE fill:#FCE4EC,stroke:#C62828,color:#B71C1C
    style MAIN fill:none,stroke:none
    style LEGEND fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#ccc,color:#666

    classDef ai fill:#E3F2FD,stroke:#1565C0,color:#0D47A1
    classDef web fill:#FFF3E0,stroke:#E65100,color:#BF360C
{{/mermaid}}


