== Research Overlap ==

=== Source Attribution (ACL 2024 touchpoint) ===

The ACL 2024 //Faithful LLM Specialists// paper provides a direct touchpoint on citation fidelity and source attribution: LLMs can cite the wrong sources or misrepresent what sources say. FactHarbor addresses related concerns structurally: every verdict traces to specific evidence items with source reliability scores. A post-verdict **grounding check** (Step 5: Validator) exists but currently runs in advisory mode — it flags mismatches without blocking publication. Tightening attribution evaluation and enforcement is therefore a plausible collaboration area, not something already solved.

=== Evidence Quality Scoring (DIRAS, NAACL 2025) ===

Our evidence filter assigns //probativeValue// (high/medium/low) via LLM prompt — a categorical approach. DIRAS shows that explicit relevance definitions per query and continuous calibrated scores significantly improve scoring. Integrating DIRAS-style relevance assessment could strengthen our evidence weighting in verdict aggregation.

=== Multi-Agent Debate (Climinator parallel) ===

FactHarbor's 5-step debate is adjacent to, but not the same as, the mediator-advocate line explored in climate fact-checking systems such as Climinator. FactHarbor adds self-consistency checking, cross-provider diversity, and evidence-weighted contestation rules. Unlike domain-specific systems, this architecture is **topic-agnostic** — it works for climate, politics, health, economics, or other domains without modification.

=== Collaboration Opportunities ===

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
* **Precision / evidence-quality improvement** — formalize and benchmark our filtering with your evaluation methodology
* **Retrieval evaluation** — measure how well our iterative search captures relevant evidence
* **Source credibility benchmarking** — evaluate our multi-provider reliability scoring
* **Speed / latency reduction** — identify where pipeline time can be cut without lowering analytical quality
* **Reproducibility / stability protocols** — define tolerance bands, repeatability metrics, and evaluation procedures
* **Cost reduction** — optimize model tiering, caching, and reuse without sacrificing quality
* **Multi-agent debate architecture** — study and improve the debate pattern itself
)))

